    "title": "test: enable -Wunused-function in test suite (Fix #1831)",
    "user": {
      "login": "kallal79",
      "id": 182690849,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOCuOkIQ",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/182690849?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/kallal79",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kallal79/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "\r\nThis PR addresses issue #1831 by enabling the `-Wunused-function` compiler warning within the test suite. \r\n\r\nCurrently, `-Wno-unused-function` is passed globally to disable warnings about unused functions, making it too easy to write a test case but forget to actually call it. To catch untested helper functions safely, this PR uses GCC/Clang pragmas scoped strictly to the body of the test files.\r\n\r\n### Changes Made:\r\n- Added `#pragma GCC diagnostic warning \"-Wunused-function\"` directly after the `#include` statements in `src/tests.c`, `src/tests_exhaustive.c`, `src/ctime_tests.c`, and `src/unit_test.c`. \r\nFixes #1831 \r\n",
